Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: iScan Online, Inc. is a provider of data breach prevention solutions, enabling organizations to discover unprotected sensitive data, detect their security threats and report on the financial impact of a breach before it occurs. iScan Online was named an Industry Innovator by SC Magazine in 2013 and 2014 and the Top 20 Most Promising Enterprise Security Companies by CIOReview Magazine in April 2014. iScan Online is dramatically changing the way mid market and enterprise organizations identify unprotected sensitive data, security threats that can be used to gain access to the data and quantify the liability cost associated with a potential data breach before it occurs. Through its patented, scalable cloud delivery model and its simplified deployment practices, iScan Online customers achieve visibility into their data-breach risk exposure in minutes, not weeks or months. iScan Online provides customers with analytics and enterprise reporting that details their total estimated liability in dollars as well as prioritizes remediation efforts to prevent a data breach before it occurs.

In addition to its new construction/remodeling services, the company offers interior design services; builds outdoor living spaces/decks; performs retail renovations, high-end custom steel work and fabrication, and custom carpentry; and more. Owner-operator Benjamin Dumitrascuta is a second-generation building professional—his father, Gelu, established his own construction company in the 1980s after emigrating from Eastern Europe and taught his son the trade at a young age. “He instilled in me the importance of quality craftsmanship, and that remains my number one objective today,” says Mr. Dumitrascuta. Mr. Dumitrascuta and his wife, Roxana, take a personalized approach to dealing with clients and develop close relationships with them that continue even after their projects are finished. “Personal service is an important part of our process,” confirms Mr. Dumitrascuta. “We provide our clients with greater benefits because we offer more value by working together on interior design and construction, which eliminates a lot of wasted time and communication problems.”

Description: Beer Citizen is a social beer review app that allows its users to discover, review, and share new brews.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Beer Citizen is a social beer review app allowing beer enthusiasts to discover, review, and share new brews using a new review model based on beer trait data. Beer Citizen is a new way of reviewing beers, where a beer is evaluated by quantifying the intensity of its individual traits, and reviews from other users (or “citizens”) are combined to build a beer's overall profile.  The Beer Citizen iOS app takes this data-based review model, makes it mobile, and gives citizens the added capability to publish photos of the beers people enjoy and the breweries they visit, on the go. The free app is compatible with the iPhone, iPad, and iPod Touch. While other beer review apps and websites often focus primarily on the issue of “how good” a beer is, the objective of Beer Citizen is to create data-driven beer profiles to answer the broader beer question of “what’s it like?” by aggregating the trait data entered with every review of a beer. To review a beer, citizens find the beer they’re sampling, and add traits to one of four main categories (appearance, scent/aroma, taste/flavor, and body/mouthfeel). The relative intensity of each trait is then entered by simply adjusting a slider to note a little or a lot of that trait. During the review process, users can also add tasting notes, indicate how much they like the beer, upload photos, and check in at a location. Other features include the ability to follow other users, beers, and breweries, to add beers to their wishlist or to their cooler, and share reviews on their Facebook and Twitter feeds.
Industry Groups: Apps, Food and Beverage, Mobile, Platforms, Software

Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Switch and Data is a provider of Internet exchange and co-location services. Based in Tampa, Florida, Switch and Data operates 35 (thirty-five) high-power density Data Centers and 7 (seven) PAIX Peering Internet Exchanges throughout North America, serving more than 1,000 customers. Switch and Data's PAIX is recognized worldwide as the premier name in peering and Internet exchange services, as not only the first public peering exchange, but also home to one of the largest commercial exchange points in North America.  Company Highlights * A minimum of 20%, year over year, growth for 5 years running * $205.4M of Revenue in 2009 * Peering Exchange & Interconnection Provider to over 400 networks including the following US Tier 1 carriers: [AT&T](/organization/at-t), [Verizon](/organization/verizon), [Level 3](/organization/level-3), [Sprint](/organization/sprint), [Global Crossing](/organization/global-crossing). Facility Highlights * 2.4, 4 and 6 kW power load rated cabinets as a standard Offer (Hot Aisle Heat Containment Options available for higher power density levels) * N+1 AC Power Plant and 2N+1 DC Power Plant * Operator of the Largest East and West Coast Peering Exchange Points (NY Metro & Bay Area Metro PAIX Peering Exchanges) Content & Entertainment Practice A cross-functional Team of Engineers, Product & Marketing Managers and Sales Executives dedicated to supporting the Content & Entertainment vertical. The Practice supports Content, Media and Gaming companies on Infrastructures by designing, developing, deploying and supporting these environments. Practice Highlights * $40M in recurring revenue  * Over 25+ years of Vertical Industry Experience * Unprecedented Expertise     * Infrastructure Application     * Online Gaming (MMOG)     * Digital Distribution     * Streaming Services     * Web 2.0 & Social Networking     * eCommerce     * CDN     * Cloud and Utility based Services     * Virtualization     * Infrastructure Optimization     * Power Design     * Hardware Platform Technologies     * Geographic Placement & Municipality Expertise     * Data Center Migration     * IP Transit & Peering Services * Practice supports 21 CDNs     * Akamai & Limelight's largest vendor * Practice supports world's largest Search Engine; world's largest Social Networking Website; world's largest Software Company; all US based MSOs (cable providers) and two US based Satellite Providers In Conclusion What does Switch and Data have to do with Content & Entertainment? * Most Networks can't handle the volume generated by Content & Entertainment Providers, by placing your infrastructure at the Network Exchange Point it gives you the ability to access numerous egress points at once—removing the single network provider bottleneck. * Switch and Data offers extensive resources to deliver a high-quality end-user experience     * 5 Content & Entertainment (C&E) Regional Managers; 3 C&E Customer Solution Engineers; 3 C&E Sales Operations Support Personnel; 150 Operations Engineers; 2,000 PAIX Peering Ports; 44,170 Network Ports to ensure network reliability     * Less network hops, results in less latency, equals better performance How does Switch and Data efficiently link millions of users to online Content & Entertainment? * Switch and Data's PAIX Peering Exchanges transact more packets between networks, or content providers and networks, than any other group of Peering Exchanges in the World * Switch and Data's PAIX Peering Exchanges act as a reliable network exchange point to 97% of the world's Internet traffic * Switch and Data's Palo Alto PAIX was the first Internet Exchange in the World with more traffic going through this Site than any other location in the World * The World is going broadband and more broadband network providers connect at Switch and Data Sites and PAIX Peering Exchange locations than any other group of locations within North America
